HEADWORD: jerkwater
<hw>jerkwater</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <ety>[from <ets>jerk</ets> +
<ets>water</ets>, a place where it is necessary to draw (jerk) water to
supply the boiler of a steam engine.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>small and
remote and insignificant; <as>as, a <ex>jerkwater</ex>
college</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> one-horse, pokey, poky.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Railroads)</fld> <def>Off the main railroad
line.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

